05/08/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Republika Srpska (RS) Interior Ministry and the RS Civil Protection Service announced on Wednesday (4 August) plans to conduct a mass illegal arms confiscation operation called "Summer Harvest 2004" in western RS. SFOR personnel will support the campaign, which is scheduled to begin Tuesday. SFOR will open special collection sites in Prijedor, Bosansko Novo, Kotor Varosi and Skender for members of the public who want to turn in illegal weapons. (FENA - 04/08/04)
